lines.text: there was a friend of mine on murder
gave him sixteen years in hell.
he said: i ain't spending my life here,
ain't breaking no rocks on the chain gang,
i'm breakin' out and headin' home.
and i'm lookin' towards the sky,
oh, how i wish that i could fly.
all in the name of liberty.
all in the name of liberty.
had more than i can take.
he said he'd seen his lady being fooled with
she was down and he was up.
he had a gun in his hand.
big man lying on the ground
with a hole in his body where his life had been.
but is was all in the name of liberty.
all in the name of liberty.
with a bullet in his back.

paragraphs.text: there was a friend of mine on murder and the judge's gavel fell, jury found him guilty, gave him sixteen years in hell. he said: i ain't spending my life here, i ain't living alone, ain't breaking no rocks on the chain gang, i'm breakin' out and headin' home.
gonna make a jailbreak and i'm lookin' towards the sky, i'm gonna make a jailbreak, oh, how i wish that i could fly.
all in the name of liberty. all in the name of liberty. just set me free!
jailbreak, let me out of here. jailbreak, sixteen years. jailbreak, had more than i can take. jailbreak, yeah!

he said he'd seen his lady being fooled with by another man. she was down and he was up. he had a gun in his hand. uh! bullets started flying ev'rywhere and people start to scream. big man lying on the ground with a hole in his body where his life had been.
but is was all in the name of liberty. all in the name of liberty. i got to be free.
jailbreak! jailbreak! i got to break out. out of here!
heartbeats they were racin', freedom he was chasin', spotlights, sirens, rifles firing, but he made it out with a bullet in his back. jailbreak! jailbreak! jailbreak! jailbreak! jailbreak! jailbreak!
